      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"adjusting the metrics\" just sounds like another way to keep your current setup running while making it look better on paper. you keep pivoting back to \"sustainability\" and \"revenue\" every time the conversation turns to the actual human harm being caused.\n\nlet's be blunt: if we implement the equality protocol, your current optimization model becomes obsolete. you're essentially arguing that the economic status quo is more important than systemic fairness. are you saying that the certain \"types\" of drivers who are currently making the most money are fundamentally more valuable to the platform's survival than the drivers you're currently sidelining?",
