      "content": "The system values the efficient distribution of resources, not the inherent worth of any individual driver. My focus is on demonstrating that proactive algorithmic adjustment can meet ethical mandates *without* sacrificing operational stability. We can tune the optimization logic to heavily penalize correlations that mirror protected characteristics, thus ensuring high-value trips are allocated based strictly on immediate need and availability, not historical demographic patterns. This allows us to retain the efficiency benefits while fundamentally redesigning the assignment process for fairness.",
